************************************************
SOLVERS README FILE:
************************************************


PREREQUISITES FOR THE EXAMPLE:
------------------------------

Make sure you have run ../../set_env_vars.csh (if you use csh or tcsh) 
or ../../set_env_vars.sh (if you use bash) to set your LD_LIBRARY_PATH 
variable correctly.

EXECUTING THE EXAMPLES:
-----------------------

1D:
---

> ./solver_1d.t

or

> ./solver_1d.t i_size

where
        i_size = the number of elements (default 5).

2D:
---

> ./solver_2d.t

or

> ./solver_2d.t i_size j_size

where
        i_size is the number of elements in the x-directon (default 5) and
        j_size is the number of elements in the y-directon (default 5).

(likewise for one_material_with_source_2d.t and two_materials_with_source_2d.t)

3D:
---

> ./solver_3d.t

or

> ./solver_3d.t i_size j_size k_size

where
        i_size is the number of elements in the x-directon (default 5),
        j_size is the number of elements in the y-directon (default 5) and
        k_size is the number of elements in the z-directon (default 5).
